text=!!Placing images in pages²²To place an image into a page, enter the address (url) of the image into the markup text.  Any ''alternate text'' (used for tooltips and for browsers that do not display images) is placed in double quotes immediately following the image url.²²(:markup:) [=²http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/pc.jpg²Paper clips are fun to work with. ²=]²²Images can also be specified as [[upload(s)]]ed files (i.e., [@Attach:image.jpg@]) and using [[InterMap]] links.  Any location that ends in .gif, .jpg, .jpeg, or .png will be automatically treated as an image.  %note% (See [[#notes|Notes]] below for image files that lack extensions.)²²To create a [[link(s)]] to an image (like [[http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/pc.jpg]] as opposed to displaying the image itself), use double brackets to mark the link, as in [@[[http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/pc.jpg]]@] or [@[[Attach:image.jpg]]@].²²To have an image link to another location, use the image as the link text as in [@[[http://www.pmwiki.org | Attach:image.jpg"PmWiki"]]@].²²²!! Captions and floating images²²A caption can be added to an image using a vertical brace and the caption text.²²(:markup:) [=²http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/pc.jpg"Paper clips" | '''Figure 1'''²=]²²Normally, images are displayed "in line" with the surrounding text.  To left or right-align an image with text wrapping around it, use the [@%lfloat%@] or [@%rfloat%@] [[WikiStyles]].²²(:markup:) [=²%lfloat% http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/gem.jpg | '''Rock on!'''²The image is left-aligned, and the text wraps on the right side of the image.²²Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. ²=]²²Use the [@%lframe%@] or [@%rframe%@] styles to float an image and place a frame around the image and its caption:²²(:markup:) [=²%rframe% http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/gem.jpg | '''Rock on!'''²The image is right-aligned, and the text wraps on the left side of the image.²²Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua.²=]²²Use [@%center%@] to center an image. Use [@%right%@] to right align an image, without floating it.²²(:markup:) [=²%center%http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/pc.jpg"Paper clips" | Paper clips are fun to work with ²²%right% http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/gem.jpg | Rock on!²=]²²!!Resizing images²²To resize an image, use [@%width=50px%@] or [@%height=50px%@] in front of an image.    The [@%thumb%@] wikistyle is a helpful shortcut for [@%width=100px%@].²²(:markup:) [=²%width=50px% http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/bubble.jpg \²%height=50px% http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/bubble.jpg \²%thumb% http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/bubble.jpg²=]²²Resizing an image only affects how it is displayed in a browser; it does not reduce the transfer size of the image itself.²²Resized images using [@%thumb%@] can also be floated with frames, as well as made into links.²²(:markup:) [=²%lframe thumb% [[http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/bubble.jpg | http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/bubble.jpg"Burst the bubble"]] | [-Bubble-]²%lframe thumb% http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/pc.jpg"Clip the ticket" | [-Paper Clips-]²%lframe thumb% [[DocumentationIndex | http://www.pmichaud.com/img/misc/gem.jpg"Visit the Documentation Index"]] | [[DocumentationIndex | [-Rock On-]]]²=]²²²[[#notes]]²!!!Notes²* '''An image file that lacks a correct extension''' can be displayed by addition of a "false" extension to the URL. For example, if the url is [@http://www.example.com/script/tux@], add a fake query string on the end with the desired extension (e.g., [@http://www.example.com/script/tux?format=.png@]). ²²!!!See also²* [[Cookbook:Background Images]] - adding background images to divisions, tables and table cells. ²²!!!Credits²The images on this page were obtained from http://www.flickr.com and are redistributed under a Creative Commons License.²²%trail% <<|DocumentationIndex|>>²
